Cast Iron Piñata has been chosen to share the stage with some of Australia\'s best bands as well as artists from abroad, which includes: Airbourne, You Am I, The Screaming Jets, Closure In Moscow, Electric Mary, Casanovas, Kevin & Lucius Borich (COG), Colin Hay (Men At Work), Adalita (Magic Dirt), Lord Bishop Rocks (U.S.A. Germany) and members of The Butterfly Effect, Mammal & Pete Murray and the Stonemasons.They have had airplay on various Radio Stations including: Triple M & K-Rock and been used for for various promotional work. This summer Cast Iron Piñata is embarking on it\'s 2nd National Tour, covering much of Australia\'s prime venues. Rumours of an overseas adventure in 2012 have been confirmed with the band announcing a 30+ gig tour of Europe as they continue to build rapidly. \" We will probably be supporting you guys in 12 months.\" \" Mate, I give it six months.\" Tim Rogers \" Davey Lane after a show supporting You Am I.

Cast Iron Piñata\'s EP releases: \"Rock / Funk / Awesome\" (2010), and \"What A Coincidence You Are Insane…\" (2011) A new \"Double A-Side\" has just been released containing Brand New Singles: \"Every Time You Go\" & \"How Could You Leave Me?\" as well as a whole bunch of Bonus Content (Remixes\, 5.1 Surround Mixes & a Video).

\"Cast Iron Piñata are an extreme live band and their style is so unique everyone will be swept up in their sound.\" Forte Magazine. Geelong\'s Cast Iron Pinata have been hailed as rising stars\, kicking out their Funk Fused Rock. The young band who initially met in high school has been going from strength to strength after the release of the Debut EP \'Rock / Funk / Awesome\' in early 2010\, which has brought upon airplay on various Radio Stations including: Triple M & K-Rock.

Fuelled by homegrown influences COG, Jericco, Karnivool, Dead Letter Circus and MM9, The Soulenikoes have finished recording \'Reborn\', a 4-track ep aimed to push them onto the Australian alternate music scene. With an impressive live show and one iron-clad bond, The Soulenikoes are determined to show how they do it in the west.
Good times with the 4 best friends anyone could ever have.

Tom Milek is a singer-songwriter based in Melbourne. His music has drawn comparisons to Damien Rice, Ryan Adams and Whitley. His debut EP is available on iTunes.

What others have said: \"Tom Milek writes songs that epitomise the coming of age period and those familiar feelings of being young and in love/lust and living in the moment. No, these themes are not new, but Milek\'s vivid lyrics and slightly rough vocal delivery exude an honesty and vulnerability that makes his songs relatable.\" -Inpress \"Leaving a lot of his material very much up to interpretation, without forcing any sort of view or opinion down your throat; he really lets you make up your mind about everything he portrays in his music.\" -Wax Waves \"I love [Vicious Curves] organic feel, which sounds like the best of Ryan Adams with a bit of Whitley thrown in.\" -Sounds of Oz \"Milek draws the attention of the room every time he steps in front of a microphone; whether he’s playing to a dozen people sitting on beer infested floor, or a packed band room. A strong but vulnerable voice so addictive you wish he\’d sing his stage banter.\" -Young Folks Music \"Melbourne musician Tom Milek plays some really really gorgeous music, he\’s just released his debut EP \‘Love And Ambition\’, and the title sums up Tom\’s music quite well: it would be a bit cliched if it wasn\'t so genuine and so deftly executed. The themes of Tom\’s music may not be new, but he deals with issues of love and maturity with a vividness and starkness that is very, very Damien Rice-esque.\" -And Pluck Your Strings

Correct design is an absolutely crucial area for us to get right when promoting our shows. Our view is that good design enables the public to easily grasp a clear and clean idea of what the event aims to achieve whilst conveying all the important & neccessary information. That\'s why everything related to promoting our shows goes through trusted, established & highly trained inhouse designers. They are able to provide content for a wide variety of media types & form factors: i) Printed Media: posters, flyers, business cards, ticket printing. ii) Online Design: website coding and design. Our designers are also available for freelance work for design criteria falling outside the scope of the music industry.
Please contact us for a further listing of all our design services & their associated rates. Call 0352221186 or email us info@spinninghalf.com.au
